  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks designed to combat money laundering at national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (U.S.)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting (SAR) protocols\n\n3. Key Compliance Measures\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting large or suspicious transactions\n- Enhanced scrutiny of high-risk sectors/individuals\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Financial investigations\n- Asset seizure\n- Criminal prosecutions\n- Significant financial penalties\n\n5. Specific Sector Regulations\n- Banking\n- Securities\n- Cryptocurrency\n- Real estate\n- Casino/gambling industries\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities through comprehensive legal and regulatory approaches.",
